deck: Baldy Pate is a mob boss who looks a lot like Lex Luther.
description:
Origin

Badly Pate obviously got his name for his lack of hair is a crime boss who had a run in with the Terror. the Terror was trying to blackmail Pate into giving him half of his racket. This caused Baldy to get with Gerk Kreg as well as several other crime lords whom had all been threatened. As such they suspect each other and deal with their situations differently, but all wanting to get Terror and the Creeper whom they have been after already. the Creeper is the one that ends up taking the Terror down and the mob is left with just the Creeper to take out once again.

Creation

Baldy Pate was created by Steve Ditko in 1968. His first appearance being in Beware the Creeper 1.
name: Baldy Pate

deck: Hack Axeley is a private detective who gets murdered by the Terror.
description:
Origin

Hack Axeley is a private detective who built up a lot of evidence on several crime bosses including Baldy Pate and Gerk Kreg. This information is used by his two employees Baxter Forbes and Ida Horn to blackmail the crime bosses. Eventually this leads to the death of Mr. Axeley as he is beaten to death by the Terror also known as Baxter Forbes.

Creation

Hack Axeley was created by Steve Ditko in 1968. He first appeared in Beware the Creeper 1.
name: Hack Axeley

deck: Ida Horn was an employee of Hack Axeley until the Terror beats him to death.

Origin

Ida Horn worked for Hack Axeley. Mr. Axeley was a private detective who built up a lot of evidence on several crime bosses including Baldy Pate and Gerk Kreg. This information was used by Ms. Horn and another employee Baxter Forbes (the Terror) to blackmail the crime bosses. Eventually this leads to the Mr. Axeley's death as he is beaten to death by the Terror. A she was in league with the Terror she helps cover for the Terror even going so far as to try and help the Terror by fighting the Creeper herself in hand to hand combat.

Creation

Ida Horn was created by Steve Ditko in 1968. He first appeared in Beware the Creeper 1.

deck: Sinn is a character in the Adult Swim series Frisky Dingo. Sinn is Killface's left arm lady, since her right arm was ripped off by him.
description:
Creation

Sinn is a character who appeared in Frisky Dingo and was created by Adam Reed and Matt Thompson for Adult Swim by 70/30 Productions. The character is voiced by voice actress Kelly Jenrette.

History

Sinn was originally Killface's sidekick but after he rip's her right arm off in a fit of anger. Sinn is later fired by Killface and she would soon turn into his enemy. Sinn unites a team of super powered mercenaries which she calls her 'Sisterhood of Chaos'. This unit consisted of Valerie, Antagone, and Watley. Sinn later joins the Xtacles, using the name "Hooper," the team think Sinn is a man with breasts. Sinn would eventually became their leader, and renamed them the Decepticles. Sinn reveals to the Decepticles that she's actually a woman. They take over the Annihilatrix and plan to destroy the world, but Xander, Killface, and Taqu'il all have their own plans to stop the Sisterhood.

President Taqu'il, Xander and Killface separately plan their own offensives to stop Sinn and her group. During a fight Valerie shoots Sinn and turns around and frames both Arthur and Wendell.

Wendell decapitates Arthur when he tries to propose to Antagone. Antagone finally gives birth to her monster ant baby, which commits matricide by eating her head.Killface and Simon attempt to repair the burnt couplings on the Annihilatrix, while Stan and Taquil attempt an escape from their shot-down plane. Sinn and Valerie ask Watley to kill Antagone, while Wendell is sent by Xander to kill the giant ant baby. Both Wendell and Watley inadvertently fall in love with Antagone.

Attributes

Weight: Unknown

Height: 5'10"

Eyes: Black with white pupils

Hair: None

deck: Kelly Grogda is a female assassin at the King's Dominion Atelier of the Deadly Arts. She is considered unattractive by her classmates and is called The Troll behind her back.
description:
History

She was introduced when Shabnam and Marcus attended one of Petra's parties. Shabnam told Marcus that he was secretly planning to pick her up. However, Marcus got thoroughly intoxicated and ended up sleeping with her instead.

Days later, she surprised Marcus and Shabnam by stopping by their apartment. She announced she was pregnant and hadn't slept with anyone besides Marcus. Marcus called her a liar and left her with Shabnam as he was busy dealing with his own personal drama

Master Lin soon declared finals were to kill all the rats, those that had disobeyed the rules of the school. Shabnam quickly made his move and teamed up with several students who were not rats, including Kelly. He became the mastermind to hunt down the rats, specifically wanting Marcus dead. Kelly agreed to do whatever he wanted as she wanted revenge on Marcus as well. At first she seemed infatuated with Shabnam but was later seen emasculating him.
name: Kelly Grogda

deck: Atlantean captain
description:
Current Events

Sark was an Atlantean Captain in Aquaman's Household Guard.

He was killed by Black Manta (who stabbed him using his bladed weapons) when he noticed him setting up some explosives inside Spindrift Station.

Creation

Sark was created by Aquaman writer Dan Abnett and artists Scot Eaton and Oscar Jimenez. He made his debut in Aquaman: Rebirth #1.

Powers & Abilities

Sark is an Atlantean and possesses their typical superhuman abilities.

Superhuman Strength

Sark like all Atlanteans has some degree of superhuman strength.

Enhanced Durability

Sark like all Atlanteans has some degree of enhanced durability.

Underwater Adaptation

He can function normally underwater and is able to withstand the high pressures and extreme temperatures of the deep.

Leadership

He is a captain of Aquaman's Household Guard and in charge of other Guardsmen.

deck: Atlantean terrorist from the Ninth Triad and leader of the Deluge.
description:
Current Events

Corum Rath is currently a prisoner in the Penintentiary Vault, the prison of Atlantis, after his failed attack on the surface world.

Creation

Corum Rath was created by Aquaman writer Dan Abnett and penciler Scot Eaton. He made her debut in Aquaman: Rebirth #1.

Major Story Arcs

The Drowning

Corum Rath is the leader of The Deluge, a fiercely xenophobic and traditionalist Atlantean terror cell that tries to attack Boston but is stopped by Aquaman. The Deluge recruits from the Ninth Tride or the "Ninth House" of Atlantis.

He is later seen as a prisoner in Atlantis, where he denies any involvement with the attack on the USS Ponchartrain.

Powers & Abilities

Corum Rath is an Atlantean and possesses their typical superhuman abilities.

Superhuman Strength

Corum Rath like all Atlanteans has some degree of superhuman strength.

Enhanced Durability

Corum Rath like all Atlanteans has some degree of enhanced durability.

Underwater Adaptation

He can function normally underwater and is able to withstand the high pressures and extreme temperatures of the deep.

Leadership

He is the leader of a militaristic terror cell.

Trained Combatant

He is a capable hand to hand fighter, being able to briefly fight off Aquaman.

Weaponry & Equipment

Animal Control Implants

Corum Rath has access to equipment that allows him to control Atlantean beasts.

Atlantean Weaponry

Corum Rath has access to Atlantean weapons and artillery.
